events.description: Following the death of the Roman Emperor Septimius Severus at Eboracum (modern York, England) while preparing to lead a campaign against the Caledonians, the empire is left in the control of his two quarrelling sons, Caracalla and Geta, whom he had instructed to make peace.
events.html: • 211 – Following the death of the Roman Emperor Septimius Severus at Eboracum (modern York, England) while preparing to lead a campaign against the Caledonians, the empire is left in the control of his two quarrelling sons, Caracalla and Geta, whom he had instructed to make peace.[1]

events.description: Zhao Kuangyin declares himself Emperor Taizu of Song, ending the Later Zhou and beginning the Song dynasty.
events.html: • 960 – Zhao Kuangyin declares himself Emperor Taizu of Song, ending the Later Zhou and beginning the Song dynasty.[2]

events.description: A strong earthquake strikes the Ionian coast of Sicily, causing tens of thousands of injuries and deaths, especially in Catania.
events.html: • 1169 – A strong earthquake strikes the Ionian coast of Sicily, causing tens of thousands of injuries and deaths, especially in Catania.[3]

events.description: Thirteen Years' War: The Secret Council of the Prussian Confederation sends a formal act of disobedience to the Grand Master of the Teutonic Knights, sparking the Thirteen Years' War.
events.html: • 1454 – Thirteen Years' War: The Secret Council of the Prussian Confederation sends a formal act of disobedience to the Grand Master of the Teutonic Knights, sparking the Thirteen Years' War.[4]

entities.name: Grand Masters of the Teutonic Knights

events.description: John Rogers is burned at the stake, becoming the first English Protestant martyr under Mary I of England.
events.html: • 1555 – John Rogers is burned at the stake, becoming the first English Protestant martyr under Mary I of England.[5]

events.description: In Edo (now Tokyo), all but one of the Forty-seven Ronin commit seppuku (ritual suicide) as recompense for avenging their master's death.
events.html: • 1703 – In Edo (now Tokyo), all but one of the Forty-seven Ronin commit seppuku (ritual suicide) as recompense for avenging their master's death.[6]

events.description: The city of Macapá in Brazil is founded by Sebastião Veiga Cabral.
events.html: • 1758 – The city of Macapá in Brazil is founded by Sebastião Veiga Cabral.

events.description: George Washington is unanimously elected as the first President of the United States by the U.S. Electoral College.
events.html: • 1789 – George Washington is unanimously elected as the first President of the United States by the U.S. Electoral College.[7]

events.description: The French legislature abolishes slavery throughout all territories of the French First Republic. It would be reestablished in the French West Indies in 1802.
events.html: • 1794 – The French legislature abolishes slavery throughout all territories of the French First Republic.[8] It would be reestablished in the French West Indies in 1802.

events.description: The Riobamba earthquake strikes Ecuador, causing up to 40,000 casualties.
events.html: • 1797 – The Riobamba earthquake strikes Ecuador, causing up to 40,000 casualties.[9]

events.description: John Marshall is sworn in as Chief Justice of the United States.
events.html: • 1801 – John Marshall is sworn in as Chief Justice of the United States.

entities.name: Chief Justice of the United States

events.description: Napoleonic Wars: Britain seizes Guadeloupe.
events.html: • 1810 – Napoleonic Wars: Britain seizes Guadeloupe.

events.description: The Chilean Navy under the command of Lord Cochrane completes the two-day long Capture of Valdivia with just 300 men and two ships.
events.html: • 1820 – The Chilean Navy under the command of Lord Cochrane completes the two-day long Capture of Valdivia with just 300 men and two ships.

events.description: The Ohio Legislature authorizes the construction of the Ohio and Erie Canal and the Miami and Erie Canal.
events.html: • 1825 – The Ohio Legislature authorizes the construction of the Ohio and Erie Canal and the Miami and Erie Canal.[10]

events.description: The first Mormon pioneers make their exodus from Nauvoo, Illinois, westward towards Salt Lake Valley.
events.html: • 1846 – The first Mormon pioneers make their exodus from Nauvoo, Illinois, westward towards Salt Lake Valley.

events.description: The Codex Sinaiticus is discovered in Egypt.
events.html: • 1859 – The Codex Sinaiticus is discovered in Egypt.[11]

events.description: American Civil War: In Montgomery, Alabama, delegates from six breakaway U.S. states meet and initiate the process that would form the Confederate States of America on February 8.
events.html: • 1861 – American Civil War: In Montgomery, Alabama, delegates from six breakaway U.S. states meet and initiate the process that would form the Confederate States of America on February 8.

events.description: The Philippine–American War begins when four Filipino soldiers enter the "American Zone" in Manila, igniting the Battle of Manila.
events.html: • 1899 – The Philippine–American War begins when four Filipino soldiers enter the "American Zone" in Manila, igniting the Battle of Manila.[12]

events.description: Second Sino-Japanese War: Harbin, Manchuria, falls to Japan.
events.html: • 1932 – Second Sino-Japanese War: Harbin, Manchuria, falls to Japan.

events.description: Adolf Hitler appoints himself as head of the Armed Forces High Command.
events.html: • 1938 – Adolf Hitler appoints himself as head of the Armed Forces High Command.

events.description: The United Service Organization (USO) is created to entertain American troops.
events.html: • 1941 – The United Service Organization (USO) is created to entertain American troops.

events.description: World War II: Santo Tomas Internment Camp is liberated from Japanese authority.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Santo Tomas Internment Camp is liberated from Japanese authority.

events.description: World War II: The Yalta Conference between the "Big Three" (Churchill, Roosevelt, and Stalin) opens at the Livadia Palace in the Crimea.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: The Yalta Conference between the "Big Three" (Churchill, Roosevelt, and Stalin) opens at the Livadia Palace in the Crimea.

events.description: World War II: The British Indian Army and Imperial Japanese Army begin a series of battles known as the Battle of Pokoku and Irrawaddy River operations.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: The British Indian Army and Imperial Japanese Army begin a series of battles known as the Battle of Pokoku and Irrawaddy River operations.

entities.name: Battle of Pokoku and Irrawaddy River operations

events.description: Ceylon (later renamed Sri Lanka) becomes independent within the British Commonwealth.
events.html: • 1948 – Ceylon (later renamed Sri Lanka) becomes independent within the British Commonwealth.

events.description: The Angolan War of Independence and the greater Portuguese Colonial War begin.
events.html: • 1961 – The Angolan War of Independence and the greater Portuguese Colonial War begin.

events.description: All Nippon Airways Flight 60 plunges into Tokyo Bay, killing 133.
events.html: • 1966 – All Nippon Airways Flight 60 plunges into Tokyo Bay, killing 133.

events.description: Lunar Orbiter program: Lunar Orbiter 3 lifts off from Cape Canaveral's Launch Complex 13 on its mission to identify possible landing sites for the Surveyor and Apollo spacecraft.
events.html: • 1967 – Lunar Orbiter program: Lunar Orbiter 3 lifts off from Cape Canaveral's Launch Complex 13 on its mission to identify possible landing sites for the Surveyor and Apollo spacecraft.

events.description: The Symbionese Liberation Army kidnaps Patty Hearst in Berkeley, California.
events.html: • 1974 – The Symbionese Liberation Army kidnaps Patty Hearst in Berkeley, California.

events.description: M62 coach bombing: The Provisional Irish Republican Army (IRA) explodes a bomb on a bus carrying off-duty British Armed Forces personnel in Yorkshire, England. Nine soldiers and three civilians are killed.
events.html: • 1974 – M62 coach bombing: The Provisional Irish Republican Army (IRA) explodes a bomb on a bus carrying off-duty British Armed Forces personnel in Yorkshire, England. Nine soldiers and three civilians are killed.

events.description: Haicheng earthquake (magnitude 7.3 on the Richter scale) occurs in Haicheng, Liaoning, China.
events.html: • 1975 – Haicheng earthquake (magnitude 7.3 on the Richter scale) occurs in Haicheng, Liaoning, China.

events.description: In Guatemala and Honduras an earthquake kills more than 22,000.
events.html: • 1976 – In Guatemala and Honduras an earthquake kills more than 22,000.

events.description: A Chicago Transit Authority elevated train rear-ends another and derails, killing 11 and injuring 180, the worst accident in the agency's history.
events.html: • 1977 – A Chicago Transit Authority elevated train rear-ends another and derails, killing 11 and injuring 180, the worst accident in the agency's history.

events.description: A coup d'état is led by Hugo Chávez against Venezuelan President Carlos Andrés Pérez.
events.html: • 1992 – A coup d'état is led by Hugo Chávez against Venezuelan President Carlos Andrés Pérez.

events.description: En route to Lebanon, two Israeli Sikorsky CH-53 troop-transport helicopters collide in mid-air over northern Galilee, Israel, killing 73.
events.html: • 1997 – En route to Lebanon, two Israeli Sikorsky CH-53 troop-transport helicopters collide in mid-air over northern Galilee, Israel, killing 73.

events.description: The Bojnurd earthquake measuring Mw  6.5 strikes Iran. With a Mercalli intensity of VIII, it kills at least 88 and damages 173 villages.
events.html: • 1997 – The Bojnurd earthquake measuring Mw  6.5 strikes Iran. With a Mercalli intensity of VIII, it kills at least 88 and damages 173 villages.[13]

events.description: The 5.9 Mw  Afghanistan earthquake shakes the Takhar Province with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VII (Very strong). With 2,323 killed, and 818 injured, damage is considered extreme.
events.html: • 1998 – The 5.9 Mw  Afghanistan earthquake shakes the Takhar Province with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VII (Very strong). With 2,323 killed, and 818 injured, damage is considered extreme.

events.description: Unarmed West African immigrant Amadou Diallo is shot 41 times by four plainclothes New York City police officers on an unrelated stake-out, inflaming race relations in the city.
events.html: • 1999 – Unarmed West African immigrant Amadou Diallo is shot 41 times by four plainclothes New York City police officers on an unrelated stake-out, inflaming race relations in the city.

events.description: The World Summit Against Cancer for the New Millennium, Charter of Paris is signed by the President of France, Jacques Chirac and the Director General of UNESCO, Koichiro Matsuura, initiating World Cancer Day which is held on February 4 every year.
events.html: • 2000 – The World Summit Against Cancer for the New Millennium, Charter of Paris is signed by the President of France, Jacques Chirac and the Director General of UNESCO, Koichiro Matsuura, initiating World Cancer Day which is held on February 4 every year.[14][15][16]

events.description: The Federal Republic of Yugoslavia adopts a new constitution, becoming a loose confederacy between Montenegro and Serbia.
events.html: • 2003 – The Federal Republic of Yugoslavia adopts a new constitution, becoming a loose confederacy between Montenegro and Serbia.

events.description: Facebook, a mainstream online social networking site, is founded by Mark Zuckerberg and Eduardo Saverin.
events.html: • 2004 – Facebook, a mainstream online social networking site, is founded by Mark Zuckerberg and Eduardo Saverin.[17]

events.description: Civic mobilizations in Colombia against FARC, under the name A million voices against the FARC.
events.html: • 2008 – Civic mobilizations in Colombia against FARC, under the name A million voices against the FARC.[18]

events.description: TransAsia Airways Flight 235, with 58 people on board, en route from the Taiwanese capital Taipei to Kinmen, crashes into the Keelung River just after takeoff, killing 43 people.
events.html: • 2015 – TransAsia Airways Flight 235, with 58 people on board, en route from the Taiwanese capital Taipei to Kinmen, crashes into the Keelung River just after takeoff, killing 43 people.

events.description: The COVID-19 pandemic causes all casinos in Macau to be closed down for 15 days.
events.html: • 2020 – The COVID-19 pandemic causes all casinos in Macau to be closed down for 15 days.[19][20]
